would-consider-striking-over-ais-threat-to-music-3484663">罢工以示抗议</a>）、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/noel-gallagher">Noel Gallagher</a> （他称假<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/oasis">绿洲</a>专辑的创作者为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/noel-gallagher-responds-to-the-ai-generated-lost-oasis-album-3451406">“该死的白痴”</a> ）和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave">Nick Cave</a> （他将其描述为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-calls-chatgpt-and-ai-songwriting-a-grotesque-mockery-of-what-it-is-to-be-human-3381620">“对它的东西的怪诞嘲弄”）。就是成为人”</a> ）。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-says-using-ai-in-music-is-like-toy-town-3505948">滚石乐队称在音乐中使用人工智能就像“玩具城”的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
